useenv lemma { \label{lemma:lemma:4.9}
    Let $\Fc_t=\Wc_t\vee\Bc_t$ for $t>=0$, assume that
    $\sigma$-fields $\Wc_t$ and $\Bc_t$ form independent increasing
    filtrations, and $\Pc_\Fc$, $\Pc_\Wc$ are $\Fc_t$-predictable and
    $\Wc_t$-predictable
    Furthermore, $(w_t,\Wc_t)$ is an one-dimensional Wiener
    process. Then for any $u\in \bigcap_{T>0}L_2(\llo0,T\rrc,\Pc_\Fc,\R)$, there
    exists a $\Pc_\Wc$-measurable process $\bar u$ such that
    $$
        \bar u(t) = \Eb[u(t) | \Wc_t] \quad "("\Pb\times\ell"-a.e.)",
    $$
    and for almost all $t$,
    $$
        \int_0^t \bar u(s)ds = \Eb?[\int_0^t u(s)ds \Bigg| \Wc_t ]?
        \quad "(a.s.)",\qquad
        \int_0^t \bar u(s)dw_s = \Eb?[\int_0^t u(s)dw_s \Bigg| \Wc_t ]?
        \quad "(a.s.)".
    $$
    \proof
    Following proof is inspired from \cite{RL}.
    To write simply, symbolically denote $Uu(t)$ by $\bar u(t)$ in the statement
    of the lemma.
}

